---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const siteName = import.meta.env.LANDING_SITE_NAME?.trim() || 'careersim.local';
const contactEmail = import.meta.env.LANDING_CONTACT_EMAIL ?? 'hello@careersim.local';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  kicker="Legal · Privacy"
  description={`How ${siteName} collects, uses, and protects the data you share when you practice interviews, negotiations, and workplace conversations.`}
  lastUpdated="May 17, 2026"
  pagePath="/privacy"
>
  <p>
    {siteName} (“we”, “our”) helps you rehearse career conversations — interviews, salary negotiations, 1:1s, and exec
    pitches — with AI personas. This page explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and what control you
    have over it. We aim for plain English. If anything is unclear, write to <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-callout">
    <strong>TL;DR</strong> · We collect the account info and session transcripts needed to give you feedback. We
    don't sell your transcripts. You can delete your account and data at any time.
  </div>

  <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
  <h3>Account data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Email address, display name, and password hash when you register.</li>
    <li>Authentication metadata (last login, IP for security alerts, session tokens).</li>
    <li>Optional profile inputs you choose to share — target role, industry, seniority — used to tailor scenarios.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Session data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Transcripts of every message you and the AI persona exchange during a simulation.</li>
    <li>Scores, scorecards, and coaching notes generated from those transcripts.</li>
    <li>Metadata such as simulation type, persona slug, duration, and completion status.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Technical data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pages visited, basic browser/device info, and approximate region — through privacy-respecting analytics.</li>
    <li>Error reports and performance traces, with personal identifiers stripped where possible.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How we use it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Run the service.</strong> Render conversations, generate AI responses, and store your session history.</li>
    <li><strong>Generate feedback.</strong> Score your performance and produce coaching notes you can revisit.</li>
    <li><strong>Improve the product.</strong> Aggregate, de-identified usage trends help us debug, prioritize new
      scenarios, and tune persona difficulty.</li>
    <li><strong>Keep you signed in safely.</strong> Detect unusual login patterns and notify you about account events.</li>
    <li><strong>Communicate.</strong> Send service-related emails (password resets, security alerts) and — only if
      you opt in — product updates.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    We do <strong>not</strong> sell your transcripts. We do <strong>not</strong> share individual session data with
    third parties for advertising. We do not train third-party models on your private transcripts.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Processors we rely on</h2>
  <p>
    To run a modern web product we share narrowly-scoped data with the providers below. Each is a “processor”
    acting on our instructions under a data-processing agreement.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AI model providers</strong> — to generate persona replies and feedback. Messages are sent in-flight
      and are not used to train their public models when the API setting permits it.</li>
    <li><strong>Hosting & CDN</strong> — to serve the site and run our backend.</li>
    <li><strong>Email delivery</strong> — to send transactional emails (signup, password reset, alerts).</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics & error monitoring</strong> — to measure usage and catch bugs, with IP truncation where
      offered.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Cookies and similar tech</h2>
  <p>
    We use a small number of cookies and equivalent local storage entries:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> — keep you signed in. Required for the app to work.</li>
    <li><strong>Preference storage</strong> — remember UI choices like theme.</li>
    <li><strong>Aggregate analytics</strong> — measure page-level usage. No cross-site tracking.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
  <p>Whatever jurisdiction you live in, you can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access</strong> the data tied to your account.</li>
    <li><strong>Correct</strong> profile fields you control.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account, which removes your transcripts, scores, and account record from our
      primary systems within 30 days, except where retention is legally required.</li>
    <li><strong>Export</strong> a machine-readable copy of your sessions on request.</li>
    <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of non-essential emails at any time.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these, write to <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> from the email
    associated with your account. We respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Active accounts: kept until you delete the account.</li>
    <li>Deleted accounts: purged from primary databases within 30 days; encrypted backups age out within 90 days.</li>
    <li>Anonymized, aggregate usage data may be retained indefinitely for product analytics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We encrypt data in transit (HTTPS) and at rest, hash passwords with modern algorithms, scope access
    on a need-to-know basis, and review our practices regularly. See our <a href="/security">Security page</a> for
    more detail.
  </p>

  <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    {siteName} is operated from the United States. If you access the service from elsewhere, your data is
    transferred to and processed in the U.S. and other countries where our processors operate, under standard
    contractual safeguards.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Children</h2>
  <p>
    {siteName} is intended for users aged 16 and older. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 16.
    If you believe a child has provided us data, contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be announced via email or an in-app
    notice. The “Last updated” date at the top of the page always reflects the most recent revision.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
